NOTICE:

not_kernel ONLY supports the following device:

r8q - Galaxy S20 FE (Snapdragon)

- Unsupported:
bloomxq - Galaxy Z Flip 5G
f2q - Galaxy Z Fold2 5G

* The above foldables are weird and it seems like the dtsi's are incomplete or something like that.

- Unsupported:
x1q - Galaxy S20 5G
y2q - Galaxy S20+ 5G
z3q - Galaxy S20 Ultra
c1q - Galaxy Note 20
c2q - Galaxy Note 20 Ultra

* The devices above uses broadcom wifi which is currently broken in LineageOS source.

- Unsupported:
gts7l - Galaxy Tab S7 (LTE)
gts7lwifi - Galaxy Tab S7 (WIFI)
gts7xl - Galaxy Tab S7+ (LTE)
gts7xlwifi - Galaxy Tab S7+ (WIFI)

* The kernel is 100% functional for the Tab's, however i don't own any of them.

To build with workflows:
Just call the codename.yml and it will build the kernel for that phone/tablet.
